headline: Why GoDaddy (GDDY) Stock Is Falling Today
summary: Shares of domain registrar and web services company GoDaddy (NYSE:GDDY) fell 8.9% in the afternoon session after the company reported underwhelming first quarter 2025 results which included a miss on annual recurring revenue.

headline: GoDaddy (NYSE:GDDY) Updates Guidance after First Quarter Revenue Hits US$1,194 Million
summary: GoDaddy (NYSE:GDDY) saw a 6.62% price increase last week, which aligns with broader market trends driven by positive economic indicators such as a strong jobs report and optimism from potential U.S.-China trade talks. The company's reaffirmation of its earnings guidance for 2025, despite the recent decline in net income and earnings per share, likely supported investor confidence. Meanwhile, the general market environment remained bullish with the S&P 500 on its longest winning streak since...
